    <context>The Spaarke platform uses workspace pages (LegalWorkspace, WorkspaceLayoutWizard) that provide configurable multi-panel layouts. These workspaces use panel splitters, configuration-driven composition, and dynamic panel loading. No architecture document captures this workspace system end-to-end.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-architecture skill structure
      - Source ALL content from actual code — do not invent workspace features
      - Document the workspace layout system (shell, panels, splitters)
      - Map panel composition: how panels are configured and composed
      - Document configuration-driven UI: how workspace config drives panel selection and layout
      - Include WorkspaceLayoutWizard: how users configure their workspace
      - Cite source files for every component
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
